cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision and machine learning techniques for face synthesis and attribute extraction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel framework based on Generative Adversarial Networks, which falls under the category of machine learning and deep learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the second most likely category. The paper also discusses the use of unsupervised learning techniques to improve the fidelity of synthesized faces, which falls under the category of unsupervised learning and reinforcement learning, i.e., cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of face frontalization and face attribute morphing, which falls under the category of multimedia and image processing, i.e., cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of adversarial example detection, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography, i.e., cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
